<ol><li>The material is held at its upper end and <b>loaded by hanging weights</b>&nbsp;at its lower end.</li><li>A set square is attached to the bottom of the weights to&nbsp;<b>measure the extension</b>&nbsp;of the material.</li><li>The weight of the load is <b>increased in steps</b> then <b>decreased to zero</b>.</li></ol><div>The measurements can be plotted as a tension-extension graph.</div>